in any of the following environments : Fintech/ Gaming / Security / Aerospace /and or Blockchain. You will have built and shipped software products or protocols with at least two production launches to speak of. Experience of managing engineering teams including building and leading productive, high-functioning, and distributed teams. Previous active participation in a team's career development, having managed engineer's performance with proper mentorship and coaching. Detailed understanding of software methodologies and processes including Agile and Kanban. Ability to work with product teams in defining tasks and creating roadmaps. Ability to foster and to create positive engineering cultures. Ability to communicate with technical and business stakeholders. NICE-TO-HAVES Previous experience in blockchain or distributed systems. Experience of working with Ethereum. Engagement in Open Source communities. Experience of scaling teams rapidly. Experience of delivering protocols rather than products. Experience working in an innovative, disruptive businesses. WHAT WE VALUE AT CLEARMATICS Collaboration and respect. Honesty & Humility. Ability to challenge ideas. Willingness to deliver robust solutions. Passion for the technology and its challenges. Continuous improvement and learning. PERKS AND BENEFITS Central London location in bright, spacious offices. Competitive salary. Flexible working and possibility to work remote. Relocation assistance. Company pension. Hardware budget to give our developers the best equipment. Professional development - annual individual Learning & Development budget. Monthly Friday company meeting with pizza and beers. \"Show and Tell\" sessions - knowledge sharing across teams. Great kitchen filled with your favorite British specialties. Join a fast-growing, game-changing, FinTech company ;) Skills Experience working in a scaling product start-up in any of the following environments : Fintech/ Gaming / Security / Aerospace /and or Blockchain. 